Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A visiting Chinese media delegation today held a 
news conference with the president of the republic, Lieutenant 
General 'Umar Hasan al-Bashir. In discussing those developments 
concerning Sudan, the president of the republic stressed the 
exceptional relations which bound Sudan to China, and said that 
those relations were witnessing a new stage of development. His 
excellency referred to Sudan's efforts to strengthen its 
relations with countries in the Far East such as China, 
Indonesia, Korea, and Pakistan. On the efforts being made to 
achieve peace in the country, Lt. Gen. 'Umar al-Bashir made 
clear that the government was keen on seeking a peaceful 
resolution to the problem of the south, pointing out that the 
war in the south was political -- and that its resolution must 
be political. He said that the government encouraged the 
efforts of the Inter-Governmental Authority on Drought and 
Development countries to achieve peace. 
  On relations between the Arab and Muslim Peoples' Conference 
and the Sudanese Government, the president said that the 
conference was a people's organization and had no official 
status or link with the government. 

